                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18170702-132-victim1035 t18170702-132-viclabel743"></join>. On the 31st of May, the rug hung at the door, a boy gave the alarm about one o'clock, and I missed it.</p>
               <p>BENJAMIN POWIS. I am a file-cutter. I saw the prisoner take the rug from the door; he was pursued and taken, he threw it into a shop in Broad-court. I am sure he is the man.</p>

               <p>WILLIAM STUBBING. I am a pawnbroker, the prisoner ran by my door, I found the rug lying at my side door.</p>
